A vintage 1950s Singapore shophouse street scene with traditional wooden carpentry workshops, but all the storefronts display blank, dusty signboards and empty window displays. In the foreground, a beautifully crafted antique wooden cabinet sits abandoned on the street, while ghostly figures walk past without noticing it. The scene is rendered in warm sepia and faded turquoise tones typical of old Singaporean postcards, with dramatic afternoon shadows casting across the five-foot way. Ornate Peranakan tiles line the corridor floors, and wooden shutters hang slightly askew. The mood is melancholic yet nostalgic, suggesting forgotten craftsmanship invisible to the modern world.
